It's insane just how Gigachadian the daily knight lifestyle was. Wake up, go on a joyride with your horse through the peasant settlement and fields. Training grounds. Get a squire to hold a shield and beat him up with your sword for fun. 4-5 hours of hunting (basically vidya).

Dinner in the castle. Boar glazed with honey and stuffed with doves and berries and a gallon of beer. Some bard is singing cool songs keeping up the Stimmung. Have sex with your wife for an hour. You have zero idea what she's even doing all day. Sleep and do it all again tomorrow

You know I'm a big anti-communism guy, but I have to admit Marxists dot org is probably the most functional website in existence. You can type "Hegel science of logic" and immediately find the raw text uploaded there. Hypertext links leading to other books. It's simply wonderful.

Primitive 2006 Internet design without tiresome stylistic choices . Raw text you can ctrl+c in browser instead of myriad scans and ebooks. Functional references. You want an obscure philosophical essay, you find it in a few clicks. Shame right-wingers don't have a similar library

Someone pointed it out, but communists have always been good at distributing their texts to people, giving pamphlets to workers, ML book clubs, etc. pretty sure Chinese embassies still mail you Mao's complete works if you write them a letter and ask. Credit where credit is due.
